We faced an eSWT bug when negative values are passed to the org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Control.setLocation(int,int) method. 
On the Windows XP plattform it works fine, but on the Windows Mobile platform (J9 ppro11, PPC 2003 SE) the same code fails. 
No error is raised, but the label and its image are only refreshed and not moved. Passing positive values works fine.
The application we build contains a scrollable composite which contains a label showing an image.
We are using the latest eRCP RC2 release.

